claim.claim-text:
1. A luminescent material having the formula:



[AaBbXxX′x′X″x″][dopants],

wherein
A is cesium;
B is tin;
X, X′, and X″ are independently selected from at least one of iodine and bromine;
the dopants are present in amounts less than 5 percent in terms of elemental composition and include electron acceptors and electron donors;
a is 1;
b is in the range of 1to 3; and
x,x′, and x″ have a sum that is 1+2b;
and wherein the luminescent material exhibits photoluminescence having: (a) a quantum efficiency of at least 20 percent; (b) a spectral width no greater than 100 nm at Full Width at Half Maximum; and (c) a peak emission wavelength in the near infrared range.

9. A luminescent material having the formula:



[AaBbXxX′x′X″x″][dopants],

wherein
A is selected from at least one of sodium, potassium, rubidium, and cesium;
B is tin;
X, X″, and X″ are independently selected from at least one of chlorine, bromine, and iodine;
the dopants are present in amounts less than 5 percent in terms of elemental composition and include electron acceptors and electron donors;
a is in the range of 1 to 9;
b is in the range of 1 to 5; and
x, x′, and x″ have a sum in the range of 1 to 9,
wherein a is 1, and the sum of x, x′, and x″ is 1+2b.
